MVP (Minimum Viable Product) in CAPS
Definition of MVP (Minimum Viable Product):
MVP is the simplest version of a product that delivers core functionalities to users while minimizing development time and effort. It allows early user feedback and validation before investing in full-scale development.
________________________________________
MVP for CAPS (Comprehensive Assessment and Preparation System)
In the CAPS project, the MVP focuses on essential features that allow students to take tests, faculty to manage questions, and administrators to oversee the process efficiently.

These core features provide the most value while keeping effort manageable.

1. User Registration & Login System
ïƒ˜	Secure login for students, faculty, program chairs, and super admins.
ïƒ˜	Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) â€“ Users have different permissions.
ïƒ˜	Basic password recovery via email.

2. Question Bank Management
ïƒ˜	Faculty can add, modify, remove but changes require approval from Program Chair/Dean.
ïƒ˜	Categorization of questions by subject, difficulty, and coverage.
ïƒ˜	Search function to quickly find questions.

3. Question Approval System
ïƒ˜	All added, modified, or removed questions require Program Chair/Dean approval.
ïƒ˜	Approval requests are logged for transparency.
ïƒ˜	Approved questions become available for test creation.

4. Basic Test Creation & Management (Including Randomization)
ïƒ˜	Faculty can create assessments from an approved question bank.
ïƒ˜	Randomization feature to avoid repetitive test patterns.
ïƒ˜	Save test drafts for future editing.

5. Student Dashboard and UI
ïƒ˜	Students experience the easiest UI/UX of the system.
ïƒ˜	Students can view test history, and performance reports.
ïƒ˜	Visual indicators (charts/graphs) for strengths and weaknesses.

6. Automated Scoring for Objective Questions
ïƒ˜	System auto-grades multiple-choice questions.
ïƒ˜	Students receive immediate feedback.
ïƒ˜	Scores are stored for performance tracking.

7. Question Printing System
ïƒ˜	Super Admins can print and authorize exam questions.
ïƒ˜	Faculty can print school-level exams.
ïƒ˜	Generates well-formatted PDFs.


